properties.headline: Winter Storm Warning issued January 20 at 2:26PM PST until January 22 at 4:00AM PST by NWS Seattle WA
properties.description:
* WHAT...Heavy snow expected above 3000 feet. Total snow
accumulations of 1 to 2 feet.

* WHERE...Cascade mountains and valleys of Whatcom and Skagit
Counties, including the Mount Baker Ski Area.

* WHEN...From 4 AM Tuesday to 4 AM PST Wednesday.

* IMPACTS...Travel could be very difficult.
properties.instruction:
If you must travel, keep an extra flashlight, food, and water in
your vehicle in case of an emergency.

For the latest road conditions in Washington state, call 5 1 1.

NWSheadline: WINTER STORM WARNING IN EFFECT FROM 4 AM TUESDAY TO 4 AM PST WEDNESDAY ABOVE 3000 FEET
